<img src="https://images.code.org/613d33bfaf85b3d47b95e2ad96c84c8d-image-1707323049639.png" alt="students holding a micro:bit" width="250px" style="border-radius:10px; float:right; margin: 0 40px 0px 40px;">

## No validation - push the creativity 
- #### Unlike some of the coding levels on the Code.org platform, MakeCode does not have validation to “pass.” 
- #### Encourage students to be creative and explore the possibilities. 
- #### Celebrate perserverance and trying new things, even if it doesn't always work.

<br>

---

## Discussion/ Share out
- #### Enrich students’ experience with physical computing by building in discussion and sharing amongst students. Students can share or demo their projects, discuss what was easy/challenging and what they liked best about the experience. 


